Double ValueType Demo
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph><Run FontWeight="Bold">Double ValueType Demo</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph>A chart can automatically compute an appropriate Double range based on the set ValueType. The Double range can also be explicitly specified setting AutoSetRange to False and then manually specifying the Interval for the chart axis.

</Paragraph><Paragraph TextAlignment="Center">
<Image Source="Images\Axis Double ValueType Demo.png" Width="750" Height="600" /></Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Features
</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">
<ListItem><Paragraph>Range and Interval of the chart axis can be auto-set or customized.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Interactive Features</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The Checkbox <Bold>"ISAutoSetRange"</Bold>helps to set the IsAutoSetRange property for the Chart Axis.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The text box <Bold>"Range"</Bold> helps to set the custom ranges. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The text box <Bold>"Interval"</Bold> helps to set the interval of Primary Axis.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
 
</List>
</FlowDocument>